<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>The Filipino-American Presbyterian Church, New Church Development (NCD) was established in 1999.  Previous to its establishment, the church started off with a few families who worshipped from house to house.  As the congregation grew, worship was then held at Greenfield Presbyterian Church, Berkley, MI.  Reverend Fred Baliad presided over worship.  The church moved to a permanent location at the Southfield Presbyterian Church under Rev. Fe Esperanza B. Ayap.  The congregation organized and participated in various activities such as community fundraisers, cultural events, charities, hosting of special guests, national conferences, and assisting new Filipino immigrants.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The Filipino-American Presbyterian Church records are organized into two series: Church History and Administrative Activities.  Together, these series contain meeting minutes, agendas, photographs, reports, publications, and correspondence.</p>
</scopecontent>

